<subSubSection id="C362449B8E58FFFFDE8EFBB7FAFDEB40" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC717108E58FFFFDE8EFBB7FAFDEB40" blockId="1.[151,1437,1040,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDE8EFBB7FE96EA21" bold="true" box="[151,276,1040,1066]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDF03FBB6FE59EA21" authorityName="Can et Gulmez" authorityYear="2022" box="[282,475,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolica">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDF03FBB6FE59EA21" box="[282,475,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Lestica anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDD3BFBB7FC03EA21" box="[802,897,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Solenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDD3BFBB7FC03EA21" box="[802,897,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Solenius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDA7FFBB6FB63EA21" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[1126,1249,1040,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDA7FFBB6FB63EA21" box="[1126,1249,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(narrowed head, shild-like foretarsomere I, spine at the base of the forefemur, hindtrochanter with ventral spine, bidentate mandibule), but differs from it by the following characters: conspicuous spine present on apex of foretrochanter (carinate in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDEACFBDAFEB1EA9D" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[181,307,1148,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDEACFBDAFEB1EA9D" box="[181,307,1148,1174]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDF54FBDBFE52EA9C" box="[333,464,1148,1175]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs. 1c, 1f</figureCitation>
); foretarsomeres II and III as broad as I (foretarsomeres II and III markedly narrower than I in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDF19FB06FEFCEAB1" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[256,382,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDF19FB06FEFCEAB1" box="[256,382,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDF81FB07FD9DEAB0" box="[408,543,1184,1211]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs. 1a, 1d</figureCitation>
); posterior part of midfemur not keeled, widened towards base, not tooth-like, but rounded (posterior part of midfemur carinate, tooth-like in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDD48FB62FC4FEAD5" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[849,973,1220,1246]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDD48FB62FC4FEAD5" box="[849,973,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDDFDFB63FBEAEAD5" box="[996,1128,1220,1246]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Figs. 1b, 1e</figureCitation>
). Another similar species is 
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDE8EFB4EFEB3EB09" box="[151,305,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDE8EFB4EFEAFEB09" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[151,301,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollmanni">L. wollmanni</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
from which 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDFD9FB4EFDC5EB09" authorityName="Can et Gulmez" authorityYear="2022" box="[448,583,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolica">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDFD9FB4EFDC5EB09" box="[448,583,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs as follows: foretarsomere widened, shield-like; its width greater than length (first foretarsomeres less widened; its width clearly less than length in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDA16FAAAFB26EB2D" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[1039,1188,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollmanni">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDA16FAAAFB26EB2D" box="[1039,1188,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. wollmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); posterior trochanter with spine (without spine in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDFCEFA96FDE8EB41" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[471,618,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollmanni">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDFCEFA96FDE8EB41" box="[471,618,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. wollmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and flagellomere I 1.5 × as long as wide (2.0–2.2 × in 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E58FFFFDAC2FA96FAECEB41" baseAuthorityName="Kohl" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[1243,1390,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wollmanni">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDAC2FA96FAECEB41" box="[1243,1390,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">L. wollmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C362449B8E58FFFCDEDEFAF3FD25E9E1" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="431" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC717108E58FFFFDEDEFAF3FD11E884" blockId="1.[151,1437,1040,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E58FFFFDEDEFAF3FED9EB65" bold="true" box="[199,347,1364,1390]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Description:</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity id="4C80BAF58E58FFFFDFA0FAF3FD93EB64" box="[441,529,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
, fore wing 
<quantity id="4C80BAF58E58FFFFDC88FAF3FD57EB64" box="[657,725,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="430" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. Dominant body colour black, with following parts light: scape dorsally, pedicel wholly dark yellow; flagellomeres completely brownish-yellow (darkening gradually from first to last); mandible with dark reddish apex; thorax completely black, tegula translucent pale brown; anterior surface of fore- and hindfemora longitudinally, and midfemur entirely yellow except base of midfemur lower surface; all tibiae yellow except for irregular brownish spots on mid- and hindtibiae. Shield-like foretarsomere completely yellow, apex and lateral edges of foretarsomeres II–IV and entire V light brown. Mid- and hindtarsomeres I yellow basally, turning brown towards ends. Maculae of terga I–VI ivory white, dot-like on each side of tergum I, broadly interrupted on II and III, slightly interrupted mesally on IV, and continuous band on V and VI. All sterna black except yellowish-white spot in middle of sternum II.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC717108E58FFFFDEDEF93FFEE4E949" blockId="1.[151,1437,1040,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Setae on dorsal part of clypeus and half of inner margin of the compound eyes dense, silvery, and appressed, completely covering integument; on frons, vertex, anterior and lateral sides of pronotum, pronotal lobe, upper part of mesopleuron sparse, long, silvery; on epicnemial carina, acetabular carina, lower edge of mesopleuron, posterior surfaces of forefemur and foretibia dense, erect, and silvery; on scutum, propodeum, mesopleuron and terga short, scarce and silvery.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC717108E58FFFCDEDEF8EBFCCBEF16" blockId="1.[151,1437,1040,2039]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,286]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="431" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">
Head in dorsal view conspicuously narrowed behind eye (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDD50F8EBFC18E96D" box="[841,922,1868,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). OOD (ocellocular distance): POD (postocellar distance): OCD (ocelloccipital distance)= 4:3.2:8. Ocellar triangle with width to length approximately 8:5.5 (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDB76F8D7FF37E9A5" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). Orbital fovea prominent, linear, and short (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDCB8F833FD76E9A4" box="[673,756,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
). Clypeus not protruding, slightly carinate medially (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDB27F833FA0DE9A5" box="[1342,1423,1940,1966]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
). Mandibule bidentate at apex, without tooth on inner margin (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDD5EF81FFC19E9D8" box="[839,923,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
). Flagellomere I 1.6 × as long as wide, apical flagellomere slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E58FFFFDFF1F87BFDBFE9FD" box="[488,573,2012,2038]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="430">Fig. 2e</figureCitation>
). Collare elongate and narrowed in front; rounded laterally. Foretarsomeres I-III dilated as almost quadrangular shield (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDC98FF30FD50EEBA" box="[641,722,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Forefemur (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDD76FF30FC3FEEB9" box="[879,957,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
) and foretrochanter with transparent spine (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDEB9FF1CFF70EEDE" box="[160,242,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
), partly concealed by long setae on femur. Mid tibia slightly curved, slender and long. Midtarsomere I obliquely cut at apex (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDF96FF78FE61EEF2" box="[399,483,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4C80BAF58E5BFFFCDFDDFF78FE61EEF2" box="[452,483,223,249]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Midfemur enlarged, without clear basal tooth (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDDE6FF78FBD2EEF1" box="[1023,1104,223,250]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" captionTargetId="figure-79@2.[155,1432,306,1650]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. (a, b, c) and L. clypeata (d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
). Hindtrochanter with ventral spine (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDEFBFEA4FEB7EF15" box="[226,309,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 2h</figureCitation>
). Tergum VII with median longitudinal groove.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0747988E5BFFFCDE8EF92AFA1FE8AE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450961" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6450961" box="[151,1437,1677,1702]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450961/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" startId="2.[151,250,1677,1701]" targetBox="[156,1431,307,1650]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5BFFFCDE8EF92AFA1FE8AE" blockId="2.[151,1437,1677,1702]" box="[151,1437,1677,1702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5BFFFCDE8EF92AFE93E8AE" bold="true" box="[151,273,1677,1701]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E5BFFFCDF0FF929FE41E8AE" authority="Can &amp; Gülmez, 2022" authorityName="Can &amp; Gülmez" authorityYear="2022" box="[278,451,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anatolica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5BFFFCDF0FF929FE41E8AE" box="[278,451,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Lestica anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5BFFFCDFDEF929FD94E8AD" bold="true" box="[455,534,1678,1702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23F76798E5BFFFCDFDEF929FD94E8AD" box="[455,534,1678,1702]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(a, b, c) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C786C938E5BFFFCDC8BF929FC83E8AE" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[658,769,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis id="B90CCB028E5BFFFCDC8BF929FC83E8AE" box="[658,769,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(d, e, f). a, d) Foretarsomeres; b, e) Midtibiae; c, f) Foretrochanters.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC717108E5BFFFCDEDEF973FD25E9E1" blockId="2.[151,1436,1748,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">
Upper part of head finely reticulate-punctate, punctures on ocellar area finer and closer, upper frons coarsely punctate with shiny interspaces. Gena very thin, sparsely punctate; interspaces shiny. Scutal punctures large, closer anteriorly and laterally, sparser medially and posteriorly. Scutellum finely and closely punctate. Mesopleuron coarsely and sparsely punctate; punctures less than one diameter apart, with shiny interspaces (
<figureCitation id="13430B958E5BFFFCDAD3F8E7FA9AE950" box="[1226,1304,1856,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1228,1252]" captionTargetBox="[159,1429,182,1203]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[158,1430,181,1204]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lestica anatolica sp. nov. ♂: a) Dorsal view of head; b) Orbital foveae; c) Clyepus; d) Mandibule; e) Antennae; f) Spine of forefemur; g) Midbasitarsomer; h) Spine of trochanter III; i) Punctuation of mesopleuron." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6450963" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6450963/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="431">Fig. 2i</figureCitation>
). Mesosternum with rough appearance, punctuation fine and irregular. Metapleuron shiny and longitudinally ridged. Dorsal surface of propodeum markedly reticulate, lateral surface longitudinally ridged. Terga shiny, punctation of terga becoming gradually smaller and closer starting from first tergum, large on first three terga. Punctation of sterna small, distributed regularly throughout surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
